raceComments: {"comment":"One of the important lead-ups to the VRC Derby is the Vase over 2040m, and some very promising 3-year-olds test themselves against each other. We put 1. OBSERVER on top after his bold effort for second in the G1 Caulfield Guineas 2 weeks ago, a race he arguably could have won had he gotten clear air in the run home. The extra 400m here suits him, and he is the one to beat. 3. OPTIONS got in the deciding stride when scoring by a nose in the Super Impose at Flemington 3 weeks ago. He will relish the extra 240m and can repeat the dose. 5. PROVIDENCE should have won a race by now and has been quite unlucky on more than one occasion, including his last run at Rosehill in the G3 Gloaming Stakes. JMac partners up with him again, and the pair merits healthy respect. 2. HIGHVOL was beaten by the wide gate in the G1 Caulfield Guineas, and will be a lot better suited to 2040m here. Include in all combinations at what will be some each-way value.","runners":[1,3,5,2],"exclusive":true}
